links.title: According to a new study, it's actually pretty hard to catch COVID-19 on a plane
links.description: Phew. Whether as a result of the sanitizing measures taken by air carriers or independently of them, it now seems like the chances of catching COVID-19 while flying are actually pretty low. According to a new study carried out by MIT professor of management science Arnold Barnett, any given traveler incurs a one in 4,300 chances of getting sick on a two-hour flight.
